The city of Shanghai has been mapping out new economic plans and goals for 2023. The metropolis's economy was hit hard by COVID-19 in 2022 but has seen a V-shaped recovery in recent months. Mayor Gong Zheng answered questions at a press conference, following the municipality's annual meetings. Earlier, in his government work report, Gong announced Shanghai's GDP target for 2023 at above 5.5 percent.